  "text": "GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links. The long sold-out Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl Collector's Edition is back in stock at Amazon ahead of the highly anticipated sequel's November 20 release. This $180 edition comes with a bunch of physical collectibles and digital goodies. If you're interested in Stalker 2's Collector's Edition, it'd be wise to order soon. Developer GSC Game World recently announced this fresh Collector's Edition print run alongside a print run for the (still) sold-out Limited Edition. Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl Collector's EditionStalker 2 is the sequel to the 2007 survival horror shooter Stalker: Shadow of Chernobyl. As an Xbox Series X|S and PC exclusive, Stalker 2 will be available on Xbox Game Pass Ultimate on launch day for Xbox, PC, and cloud streaming. A physical standard edition is also available to preorder for $60. All editions of Stalker 2 come with in-game bonuses. Here's everything you need to know about Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl preorders. Stalker 2 Preorder BonusesStalker 2 Preorder BonusStalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl preorders come with a few more bonuses than originally expected:Veteran Rifle (weapon)Tourist Suit (skin)Exclusive backpack (skin)Extra stories and songs to listen to while sitting around the campfire before/after missions. Stalker 2 Collector’s Edition $180 Stalker 2's Collector's Edition includes a statue, physical art book, exclusive steelbook. case, and plenty of other physical collectibles. You also get the DLC that comes with the Deluxe Edition, including an extra quest and numerous skins, as well as the preorder bonuses. Here's the full list of what's included in the box:Stalker FigurineArt bookSteelbook (Collector's Edition art)Letter from developersSouvenir Zone PermitSticker PackZone MapPosterPatchesToken (dog tag)Keychain with firestarterDeluxe DLC Additional questOne costume, three weapon skins (campaign)Two costumes, three weapon skins (multiplayer)It was sold out for a long time, but Amazon replenished its stock on November 16 --snag a preorder while you can. Stalker 2 Limited Edition $80 Stalker 2's Limited Edition costs $80 and includes most of the collectibles found in the pricier Collector's Edition, but it excludes the two big ticket items: the statue and the physical art book. You won't get the Deluxe Edition DLC with this version, but it does come with the preorder bonuses. The Limited Edition's steelbook case has different art than the Collector's Edition case.Steelbook (Limited Edition art)Letter from the developersSouvenir Zone PermitSticker PackStandard DLCZone MapPosterPatchesToken (dog tag)Keychain with firestarterLetter from the developersStandard DLCThe Limited Edition is currently sold out, but it might be available to preorder again soon.A digital-only Deluxe Edition is also available to preorder on Steam, Epic, and the Xbox Store for $80. It comes with the following goodies:Additional questDigital Art bookOfficial SoundtrackOne costume, three weapon skins (campaign)Two costumes, three weapon skins (multiplayer) Stalker 2 Ultimate Edition $350 It's not available to preorder at this time, but Stalker 2's Ultimate Edition costs nearly twice as much as the Collector's Edition. It comes with everything from the CE as well as a Stalker backpack and the Artefact Container Lamp, both of which look pretty cool.Stalker backpackArtefact Container LampStalker FigurineArt bookSteelbook (Ultimate Edition art)Letter from developersSouvenir Zone PermitSticker PackDeluxe DLCZone MapPosterPatchesToken (dog tag)Keychain with firestarterThe Ultimate Edition has to be purchased from the official Stalker 2 website. Get Dark Souls Board Game For Only $51 And Roleplaying Sourcebook For $30 PS5 Pro Disc Drive Is Sold Out At Most Retailers, But Walmart Has It (For Now) The PS5 Pro Is Available Now And Eligible For One-Day Delivery At Amazon + Show More More Gami